##On New Year's Eve, I received an urgent assignment to design Thor Mountain

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Huazhong University of Science and Technology

When Yang Xuetao and his old high school classmates discussed recording the song "hand in hand, " everyone suddenly learned from the group that one of Hu Xiaofang's classmates had been ordered to take the job, she took on a key mission to fight new pneumonia -- Planning for Mount Thor. Surprised, they liked it.

This is responsible for the design of the Thunder Mountain Hospital "younger sister" , is Qiu Zhengyan, she is a design from the south-central design and Construction Hospital Medical Health Department of the director of the designer.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qiu Zhengyan (left) checks with the contractor on the location of a series of computer rooms next to the sewage treatment station. Photo courtesy of the respondents

On the evening of January 24, the evening of New Year's Eve, the central and Southern Design Institute received this urgent task: At noon on January 25, it was to give a preliminary report to Wuhan on the design of the hospital, on the morning of the 27th, the preliminary construction design drawings of the hospital will be delivered to the contractor, 27th at 11:00 am, the first module of the building began construction. Design and construction, press the fast forward button to start, leaving the design of only three days.

Qiu Zhengyan said that on this New Year's Eve, everyone was tense. At 8:30 p.m. , he received a notice to inspect the site. A meeting was held at 10:00 to discuss the site. The design was started at 11:00. The design proposal was presented at noon the next day, 12 hours'time, i and my colleagues will design a large Infectious Disease Hospital with a capacity of 1,500 beds.

During the Lunar New Year, many of the key technical personnel had already left Wuhan. The head of Qiu Zhengyan's medical and health department and two designers came to the scene. After receiving the task, the different departments of the south-central Architectural Design Institute have made up more than thirty designers of the building structure, water and electricity, HVAC, air-conditioning, economy and so on

"These nights I sleep thinking about the construction site in order to catch up on work, and I don't want to miss important calls. I check my phone first thing in the morning. Every day I work with my hands on, typing, drawing and answering the phone at the same time, " Qiu said, "When I'm really stressed, I don't feel tired or want to relax, the only thing I feel is that I don't have enough time. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qiu Zhengyan and the chief technician are on site to see the construction of the medical and technical area. Photo courtesy of the respondents

The oratory of Qiu Zhengyan

New Year's Eve emergency

After dinner on January 24, my parents and I watched the Spring Festival gala together. I chatted on my laptop and watched the reports of the epidemic. At 8:30, the Director of the Health Care Division called to tell me to go to the scene. The time was tight. He didn't say why. He just said, "we're going to see the scene. At Jiangxia District's, can you come? "

When he said Jiangxia District, I knew it had to be something like that. On the 23rd, I got a message from a student of CITIC General Institute of Architectural Design and research. I know that the Fire God Mountain Hospital has started. In fact, we are also preparing, as a medical architect, on January 23, Wuhan announced the closure of the city, I began to search on the Internet during the SARS period, "Xiaotangshan" design information, in case of emergency.

Because we couldn't get to Jiangxia District without a car, we decided to go straight to the 10:00 meeting. Everyone was called on short notice, and by the time I got to the conference room, they were already back, and there was no time to communicate in the conference room, so let's get down to business. The address was chosen in advance, and we discussed technical aspects of the building, such as the zoning of the isolation hospital, the size of the building, and so on. Leishenshan hospital site in Jiangxia Junyun village canteen, the original project is our company EPC general contract construction, we are familiar with all aspects of this plot. Notice after the meeting, scheduled for January 25 noon to the Wuhan Municipal Government report.

After the meeting, there was a sense of tension, but more time concerns. In fact, the Central and southern hospital has done hundreds of hospital projects. Technically, it is still confident, but not many designers can work on the spot during the holidays, a lot of technical backbones are not in Wuhan, the designer that our department attends a meeting that day only two people.

I am mainly responsible for the overall planning of the project, land analysis, construction scale calculation, and so on. The node task is to report the plan to the government departments the next day. So I first collated the outline of the report, do a good PPT framework, sent to the relevant professional personnel, requested the next day before 10 o'clock summary.

The one-hour session provided only a general direction for the building programme, which was difficult to define. The difficulty of design lies in the fact that time is short, it is difficult for us to fully discuss and think, we must solve the problems in our own profession independently, and at the same time, we must take into account each other and come up with feasible and effective solutions in a short time. In fact, the biggest problem or this site is relatively tight, it is difficult to arrange the 1500-bed unit, while taking into account the vehicle entrance, wind and other factors. We tried several layouts and identified one or two relatively feasible directions.

It's an urgent project that everyone works on very quietly, and it's much more effective when everyone has a common goal, as opposed to the kind of discussions and arguments that we usually have in design, says Split Second, a design consultant at the University of California, Berkeley.

The final draft is out!

At 2 am on the 25th, we gradually settled on the layout of the building and made two alternative plans as we tried to demonstrate it. At 1:30 pm to Wuhan Municipal Government report, the government convened various departments, environmental protection bureau, Fire Bureau, Planning Bureau and so on. I mainly report the general layout of the planning program, the scale of construction, and then ask the various departments to make decisions. The meeting was attended by about twenty people. The meeting room was not large and the u-shaped table was very compact. The leaders were also very efficient, meeting within an hour to form a basic idea, we immediately returned to the company to deepen the design.

With the basic planning scheme, the construction side of the third bureau has begun construction preparations, they have not yet got the drawings, only the preliminary general plan, will start to deal with the site. We continue to deepen the program. The next step is to produce preliminary construction drawings on the 27th.

During the design process, there will be various adjustments and changes in the scheme. For example, the medical technology department, which has intensive-care unit, CT examination, negative pressure operating room, these things have to cooperate with a lot of content. In the clear area of the design drawings, I made communication with the construction side, we need to determine as soon as possible medical technology design and construction units to cooperate with us, so as to avoid affecting the progress of construction in the area. There are garbage disposal, sewage discharge, and other issues, this is not a simple design process, but also involves the selection of materials, equipment, dosage, so many units need to coordinate together to determine the effective implementation of the program.

Deepening the process of drawing, the need for multi-party cooperation. During that time, I kept making phone calls, contacting the equipment manufacturer and different sub-design units to determine a lot of details in the construction drawings. Every day, I was on speakerphone, typing while drawing while talking on the phone. In addition, there are a lot of online video conference, talk a lot, I had pharyngitis, talk more cough more, so now the end of the project for a long time cough is not good.

January 25 to 30 this few days, is the design intensity highest period of time, the meal is ordered by the unit centralism, has the box meal to send in. I also rarely go home and sleep in my office COT for three or four hours at a time when the task is particularly stressful. I don't have time to get tired or relax. The only thing I feel is that time is passing too quickly.

From my home to the unit will pass by Wuhan Seven hospitals, it is the designated hospital fever clinic, the hospital gate line many people, New Year's Eve the first time to go to the meeting, I specifically took a detour to avoid seven hospitals. But after going to work is not a detour, just ride to the other side of the road, put on glasses, add a mask, still want to save time.

During the construction process, we need to communicate with the contractor, the Health Committee and the hospital to demonstrate the details of the process. The hospital has also given a lot of modification opinions, so in addition to the construction side of the problem, but also to take into account the management and use of the department. The drawing has also been changing until the 31st drawing is basically stable, no major changes, February 1 we do in the office finishing and finishing work, the final construction drawing is basically completed.

A challenge I've never faced before

After the handover, I had time to go to the construction site in the afternoon of February 2. I went to the site almost every day until it was dark and I was out of sight.

The purpose of going to the construction site is to check the conflict between the construction site and the drawing, and the difficulties in the actual implementation of the site in order to make reasonable modifications to the design. There is always on-site project management, but many of the details on the drawings or specific designers more clear, so we go to the site to solve the problem is also very necessary.

The site is basically constructed according to the drawings, but there will be some practical problems that have not been considered before. For example, sewage treatment station, the actual equipment buried deep is particularly large, site operation is limited, resulting in a series of adjacent rooms have to change the location, such as disinfection and medicine room, garbage treatment room. The space is limited, and each house has certain requirements for the distance of pollution protection to be considered, so the number of adjustments is very high. After making standard adjustments to the distance between the houses through field measurements time and time again, to get it into a tight fit.

Central South Hospital set up the medical and health department last year, but I have worked for more than ten years to design a lot of hospitals. In the large general hospital inside the general plan will have infectious building, we have done, but the specialized infectious disease hospital each city will not be too many. Like this design-and-build, 10-day design to build the emergency hospital only once.

At first, I was very excited to be involved in the construction of the Raytheon Mountain Hospital. I thought I could do something for the prevention and control of the epidemic in Wuhan. But after putting in, worry is a lot: time is tight, task quantity is very big, especially 5 before check and accept, very worry.

I remember my first project as a professional responsible person is the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, it was my third year of work. After winning the bid, it was very difficult for the hospital to reach an agreement. We made 20 or 30 plans before and after the bid. Basically, we had to come up with two or three plans to choose from every week. The design process alone took less than half a year.

The normal project construction cycle is very long, the provincial hospital of traditional Chinese medicine project is 2010 to determine the program, early 2011 out of the drawings, only to be completed in August 2014. In the past the site would not be particularly frequent, the time is to report on the program every week, three or four times a year after the start of construction. The construction of a regular project is completely different from the construction of Mount Thor. We give them a complete set of drawings, and basically we just follow the drawings. Rarely, as at Thor Mountain, do designs need to be modified based on the actual equipment or materials that can be deployed.

Thor Mountain has been built

On the way to the site, there were a lot of workers, working 24 hours a day, some working, some taking shifts. There were a lot more workers on the site than we normally go to, a lot more. Two blocks away, the construction site began to restrict traffic. In the area where we waited for the trucks, we could see big trucks from all over the country waiting in long lines, each one loaded with goods. The banner on the car said roughly where to build Wuhan Thunder Mountain Hospital, many manufacturers sent various equipment and materials, containers, air conditioning, television, and so on.

February 5 to be delivered for acceptance, the total construction area of Raytheon Mountain Hospital about 80,000 square meters, even 50,000 square meters of the hospital, the shortest construction time will be three years. Construction was still under way on the 4th, when it was raining lightly and there was water in many places. The whole construction state was very busy. On the same day we checked the initial acceptance of the area, in fact, to rectify the place is still a lot of, the rain brought a lot of inconvenience to the site, wiring will appear a lot of security risks, workers are also very inconvenient to operate. But the workers are also very efficient, after overnight rectification. Partial delivery was completed by the 5th, and construction continued in other areas.

Raytheon Mountain has more than 30 wards, 5 acceptance is two of the district, the other areas in the next few days were completed. Although the drawings are finished, but there are still many calls every day, the construction side will always communicate with me and adjust, there will be some media interviews and manuscripts. Colleagues have to work non-stop to do the renovation of the shelter hospital, these tasks are also very urgent, basically within a day or two to complete.

Now the work is not so tense, but some time ago the state of work has not been transferred, will wake up at 6:30. Too long fatigue is hard to recover in a short period of time, just finished the design period of Mount Thor Hospital, eat breakfast will sleep again, basically have a task to work from home, and then catch up on all the time to catch up on sleep.

Mount Thor Hospital has been put into operation, but the end of the epidemic is the end of the mental tension can end. I have always thought that architects are a profession with a certain social responsibility, and this time participating in the design of the Thor Mountain Project has made me realize deeply that although we, as medical architects, do not struggle in the front line like medical workers, but it's also important that the pursuit of better and better architecture brings a sense of safety and shelter to the patients, the staff, and everyone else who is busy.

(instructors: Huazhong University of Science and Technology, Zhou Tingting; paper.cn, Zhang Xiaolian, Cui Xuan)
